Class Client

java.lang.Object
model.Client
public class Client extends Object
Represents a client (customer) in the casino system. Stores personal information and account balance.
Since:
2.0
Author:
Davitroon

  • Constructor Details

    • Client

      public Client(int id, String name, double balance)
      Minimum constructor for creating a client for playing purposes. Only the ID, name, and balance are required.
      Parameters:
      id - Unique client ID
      name - Client's name
      balance - Client's current balance
      Since:
      2.0

    • Client

      public Client(String name, int age, char gender, double balance)
      Constructor for creating a new client with full information. The client is marked as active by default.
      Parameters:
      name - Client's full name
      age - Client's age
      gender - Client's gender (e.g., 'M', 'F', etc.)
      balance - Client's initial balance
      Since:
      2.0

    • Client

      public Client(String name, int age, char gender, double balance, int id, boolean active)
      Complete constructor for a client with all fields specified.
      Parameters:
      name - Client's full name
      age - Client's age
      gender - Client's gender
      balance - Client's balance
      id - Client's unique ID
      active - Whether the client is active or inactive
      Since:
      2.0
